This week's economic, banking and P&C insurance news, from an enterprise risk management perspective. Read it here...

ANALYSIS
http://email.eRisks.com/cgi-bin10/flo?y=eIYV0BHCKe0CjE0B4V0AM
How stress testing has become a key tool for risk managers.
Why are insurers missing out on the surety bond market?
Will changes in Washington affect financial privacy regulations?

CASE STUDY
http://email.eRisks.com/cgi-bin10/flo?y=eIYV0BHCKe0CjE0IXZ0A8
The Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case has been described as the biggest banking fraud in history. In the latest addition to ERisk's growing collection of Case Studies, Lisa Royan and Penny Cagan of Zurich IC Squared examine the failures of risk management that allowed BCCI's fraud to go unchecked for so long. The case study includes a chronology and a list of Web resources.

